around since 2009
It reuses JS, meaning a front-end JS developer can build an entire server themselves
it's easily extendable: numerous plugins exist to expand the capabilities of Node
fast-implementation, which allows for the creation of an entire working server with only a few lines of code. 
single-threaded asyncronous model - meaning it can handle multiple requests simultaneously and not get bottlenecked.